abstract: ST. PETERSBURG, March 31. -- The police have nipped a plot to start an uprising in the Caucasus. Yesterday they arrested seventy men, including several army officers, who as members of a revolutionary organization were engaged in providing arms, ammunition, and funds for the projected movement. A large number of military rifles and several thousand cartridges destined for the Caucasus also fell into the hands of the authorities.

Hunter, who was with the Nashville Club last season, finished the game.

abstract: That real opera bouffe has not lost its charm for New York audiences was evinced last night at the New Amsterdam Theatre at the revival of Edmond Audran's opera, "The Mascot." abstract: Not all of England's great poets are buried in Westminster Abbey. The ashes of SHAKESPEARE, MILTON, KEATS, SHELLEY, and GRAY are not there. abstract: PLATTSBURG, N. Y., April 22. -- The water of Lake Champlain is within a few inches of the highest mark on record. Last Summer, during the drought, a new low-water record was made. abstract: BEIRUT, April 25. -- The situation in Asiatic Turkey is one of extreme gravity. How many thousands have been massacred cannot even be estimated, because the disturbances have been so widespread that it is impossible to secure details of the happenings during the past ten days. The latest estimates of the number killed in the vilayet of Adana reaches approximately 25,000, and thousands have been done to death in the towns of other districts.

abstract: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y., April 25. -The local police made important discoveries to-day in connection with their arrest yesterday of four persons on charges of counterfeiting. They also found $20,000 in counterfeit money, consisting of $10,000 counterfeit American bills, and the balance in Italian bills.

abstract: CONSTANTINOPLE, April 25, 5 P.M. -- The Yildiz Kiosk capitulated at noon to-day. The garrison of 4,000 Albanians surrendered unconditionally, were disarmed, and marched out of the palace under escort of the Macedonian Army. This action was the result of long negotiations between the Sultan, Tewfik Pasha, the Grand Vizier, and Edhem Pasha, Minister of War, on one side, and Chefket Pasha, commander of the Parliamentary Army, on the other.

abstract: ADANA, Saturday, April 24. -- The emergency hospitals established here contain 300 patients suffering from wounds, many of whom are women. The average number of wounds to each patient is four. There is very great and immediate need for food and medical supplies. Practically the entire Armenian population of Adana, 15,000 people, is homeless.
